# Level 4 Workflow: Complex System

Level 4 tasks are too large to plan and execute in one pass. They are composed of multiple L1/L2/L3 sub-runs, each corresponding to a milestone. `/niko` manages the milestone list — checking off completed sub-runs, cleaning inter-run state, and routing to classification for the next milestone. There are no dedicated Level 4 build phases — those happen inside each sub-run at its own level.

## Workflow Overview

```mermaid
graph TD

    Start(("🧑‍💻 /niko"))
    CheckIfMilestones{"memory-bank/active/milestones.md<br>exists?"}

    subgraph Init["First L4 Run"]
        NikoPlan["😺 plan<br>(generate milestones)"]
        NikoPreflight{"😺 preflight"}
        ManualReview["🧑‍💻 review plan"]
    end

    subgraph NikoRouting["/niko State Routing"]
        CheckMilestoneCompletion{"All milestones<br>complete?"}
        Capstone[/"🧑‍💻 /niko-archive (capstone)"/]
        Capstone --> Done("Done")
        PrevDone{"Sub-run<br>complete?"}
        CheckOff["Check off completed<br>milestone in milestones.md"]
        Cleanup["Clean sub-run state"]
        Resume["Resume sub-run<br>workflow"]
    end

    subgraph SubWorkflow["L1-L3 Milestone Execution"]
        Classify(("😺 Classify milestone<br>as L1/L2/L3"))
        SubRun("😺 Run L1/L2/L3 workflow")
    end

    Start --> CheckIfMilestones

    CheckIfMilestones -->|"No"| NikoPlan
    NikoPlan --> NikoPreflight
    NikoPreflight -->|"FAIL"| NikoPlan

    NikoPreflight -.->|"PASS"| ManualReview
    ManualReview -.->|"🧑‍💻 /niko"| Start

    CheckIfMilestones -->|"Yes"| CheckMilestoneCompletion
    CheckMilestoneCompletion -.->|"Yes"| Capstone

    CheckMilestoneCompletion -->|"No"| PrevDone
    PrevDone --"Yes"--> CheckOff
    CheckOff --> Cleanup --> Classify

    PrevDone --"No"--> Resume
    Resume --> SubRun

    Classify --> SubRun
    SubRun -.->|"Sub-run complete<br>🧑‍💻 /niko"| Start
```

> Legend:
> - 🐱 = Phase executed autonomously
> - 🧑‍💻 = Phase initiated by operator with explicit command
> - Solid edge = Transition does not require operator input
> - Dashed edge = Transition requires operator input

The following require operator input; if you have arrived at one of these transitions, STOP and wait:

- Sub-run complete → next `/niko` invocation (operator decides when to continue)
- All milestones checked → capstone archive (operator invokes `/niko-archive`)
- Initial L4 milestone generation → first workflow execution (operator invokes `/niko`)

## Phase Mappings

To execute a phase for a level 4 task:

1. Update `memory-bank/active/progress.md` to indicate completion of the phase you are leaving.
2. 🚨 ***CRITICAL:*** Commit all changes - memory bank *and* other resources - to source control using a conventional commit in the following format: `chore: saving work before [phase] phase`.
3. Read and follow the instructions in the appropriate locations:
    - **Level 4 Plan Phase**: Load `.cursor/rules/shared/niko/level4/level4-plan.mdc`
    - **Level 4 Preflight Phase**: Invoke the `niko-preflight` skill
    - **Level 4 Archive Phase**: Load `.cursor/rules/shared/niko/level4/level4-archive.mdc`
